## Algebra / Uniswap interoperability interfaces  (Rayls first-party, BUSL-1.1)

`rayls-contracts/` declares three minimal Solidity interfaces used by the Rayls
`FeeAggregator` to interoperate with on-chain Algebra Integral (Uniswap-V3-style) pools and
the periphery swap router:
- `src/interfaces/IAlgebraPool.sol`
- `src/interfaces/ISwapRouter.sol`
- `src/interfaces/callback/IAlgebraSwapCallback.sol`

These interfaces were independently declared from the published contract ABI solely to call
deployed Algebra contracts. They are **not** derived from, and contain no source copied from,
the Algebra or Uniswap codebases, and are therefore not subject to those projects' licenses.
They are Rayls-authored first-party code, licensed under BUSL-1.1.

